title: Canton of Saint-Laurent-du-Var-Cagnes-sur-Mer-Est
text:
The Canton of Saint-Laurent-du-Var-Cagnes-sur-Mer-Est is a former <a href="France">French</a> <a href="Cantons%20of%20France">canton</a>, located in the <a href="arrondissement%20of%20Grasse">arrondissement of Grasse</a>, in the <a href="Alpes-Maritimes">Alpes-Maritimes</a> "<a href="Departments%20of%20France">département</a>" (<a href="Provence-Alpes-C%C3%B4te%20d%27Azur">Provence-Alpes-Côte d'Azur</a> "<a href="Regions%20of%20France">région</a>").
History.
The canton was created in 1982 adding part of <a href="Cagnes-sur-Mer">Cagnes-sur-Mer</a> to the pre-existent Canton of Saint-Laurent-du-Var. It was disbanded following the French canton reorganisation which came into effect in March 2015.

Description.
Only the eastern part Cagnes, close to the borders with <a href="Cros-de-Cagnes">Cros-de-Cagnes</a>, is part of this canton. The town is also part (and <a href="Chef-lieu">seat</a>) of the cantons <a href="Canton%20of%20Cagnes-sur-Mer-Centre">Cagnes-sur-Mer-Centre</a> and <a href="Canton%20of%20Cagnes-sur-Mer-Ouest">Cagnes-sur-Mer-Ouest</a> ("C. West").
